@startuml llm-key-lifecycle
' The six-step life of an LLM API key: one namespace, two readers, never copied, never in an agent.
' Source of truth: docs/src/security/credentials.md
!include _style.puml

skinparam wrapWidth 420
skinparam maxMessageSize 340

actor "Platform\nengineer" as PE #FFE4B5

box "a user namespace" #FCFCFC
  participant "**Agent** Pod" as AG #E6E6FA
end box

box "agentry-system" #F0F4F0
  participant "**Secret**\nanthropic-api-key" as SEC #FFD580
  participant "**Operator** SA\nagentry-controller" as OP #87CEEB
  participant "**Gateway** SA\nagentry-gateway" as GW #90EE90
end box

participant "**LLM Provider**\n(outside the cluster)" as LLM #FFE4B5

== 1. Stored ==

PE -> SEC : create agentry-system/anthropic-api-key
note over SEC #FFF8DC
  Created and managed by platform engineers.
end note

== 2. Referenced ==

note over AG, GW #FFF8DC
  ModelProvider.spec.credentialsRef names this Secret. Read access
  is limited to exactly **two** ServiceAccounts, and both grants are a
  namespaced Role in agentry-system, never a ClusterRole:
  **gateway** get, watch  |  **operator** get, list, watch
end note

== 3. Loaded ==

GW -> SEC : get + watch, at startup
SEC -> GW : key material
note over GW #90EE90
  Held in **process memory** for the
  life of the process. The gateway
  uses it on every proxied request.
end note
OP -> SEC : get, once per health probe
SEC -> OP : key material
OP -> LLM : GET /v1/models health probe\n(the probe needs the key: the\nendpoint requires authentication)
note over OP #87CEEB
  Held **transiently**, for the duration of one
  probe. The operator retains no key material
  between probes.
end note

== 4. Used ==

AG -> GW : LLM request over mTLS,\ncarrying **no credential**
GW -> LLM : upstream request: the gateway **injects** the\nAPI key on the agent's behalf, on this leg only
LLM -> GW : completion
GW -> AG : completion, **still no credential**
AG -[#B71C1C]->x SEC : agent cannot read agentry-system Secrets:\nnot mounted, and no RBAC to fetch them
note over AG #E6E6FA
  **Retention: never.** The agent Pod
  holds no key material at any point.
end note

== 5. Rotated ==

PE -> SEC : update the Secret in place
SEC -> GW : the gateway's Secret watch fires
GW -> GW : refresh in-memory credentials,\n**no restart**, in-flight requests\nfinish on the old key

== 6. Never copied ==

note over AG, LLM #FFF8DC
  There are no per-agent and no per-namespace copies. The Secret in
  agentry-system is the single authoritative location. **That is why step 5**
  **is one update and one watch:** with no fan-out copies there is exactly
  one place to change and one watch to fire.
end note

legend bottom
  **Read the negative space.** No credential-bearing arrow ever crosses out of agentry-system. The key
  reaches the provider on the gateway's upstream leg and nowhere else, so the agent never holds it, and
  the three holders retain it differently: **gateway** in memory for the process lifetime, **operator**
  only for the length of a probe, **agent** never. Agent Pods are additionally blocked from calling
  providers directly by NetworkPolicy: see Protecting Agent Containers from LLM Provider Access.
endlegend
@enduml
